            . I was working for Mr. Basset, in <placeName id="t18230910-185-crimeloc1020">Argyle-place, Regent-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-185-crimeloc1020" type="placeName" value="Argyle-place, Regent-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-185-crimeloc1020" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-185-off1018 t18230910-185-crimeloc1020"></join>. In consequence of missing tools, I concealed myself on the shop floor, and about half-past twelve o'clock at noon I saw the prisoner come in and take this plane and square off the floor, and put them into his pocket. I came out and took him. He said he had come in for shelter from the rain. He belongs to the Philanthropic Society.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ALLEY. Q. Could he put the plane into his pocket. Did you not say at the office you found them near where he stood - A. No; I took them out of his pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
